# ============================================================
# Duck Store — per-stack configuration
# ============================================================
# Each compose "stack" (warehouse, store, …) has its own env file
# checked into the repo:
#   - .env.warehouse
#   - .env.store
#
# run.sh passes --env-file to compose automatically. These files
# don't contain secrets, just host ports, instance name, DB name,
# and the frontend's display title. See those files for the real
# values; this is a reference for what a new stack would need.

INSTANCE_NAME=<short name, e.g. warehouse>
FRONTEND_TITLE=<human-readable, e.g. "Duck Warehouse">
BACKEND_HOST_PORT=<host port for the backend, e.g. 4001>
FRONTEND_HOST_PORT=<host port for the frontend, e.g. 5173>
MONGO_DB_NAME=<database name inside this stack's Mongo>

# ---------- future secrets (none today) ----------
# When/if auth lands, uncomment and fill in. Never commit real creds.
# MONGO_USER=duckstore
# MONGO_PASSWORD=
